{
  "texts": [
    "Research based on OGER involves the construction of a dictionary or ontology to perform dictionary matching.",
    "While we extracted lists of entities from the corresponding ontologies to perform data augmentation, our model does not require dictionary matching and all the preprocessing steps associated with it.",
    "Leveraging the power of transformer architectures, data augmentations, and transfer learning, we aimed at training a model capable of recognising patterns of how entities present themselves in texts, not only in one language but in two.",
    "As shown in Table 3, in comparison to the second-best-scoring system, the top system outperforms systems in the literature for the same dataset by + 7.33 F1 score points (Crichton et al., 2017).",
    "The top-performing system by Furrer et al. (2021) is a combination of BioBERT and OGER, which uses a dictionarybased approach and fares better than our best-performing system by only 0.46 F1 score points."
  ]
}